775	\subsection{toModuleKSheaf specialisation on a curve (iter-030)}
776	
777	The iter-029 sheaf-parameterised LES specialisation \ref{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_HModule_prime_sequence} keeps the sheaf $F$ as a generic argument. Iter-030 binds $F := \toModuleKSheaf\,C$ for $C : \mathrm{Over}\,(\Spec\,k)$, producing a curve-specific specialisation that downstream Serre-finiteness work consumes. The body is a direct application of the iter-029 sheaf-parameterised LES; the curve-specific data is supplied via the dot-notation $S.\HModulePrimeSeq$ method-call against $S : C.\mathrm{left}.\AffineCoverMVSquare$ (which sidesteps the iter-029 sub-namespace shadowing trap that required a $\mathtt{\_root\_}$ disambiguation in the abstract specialisation's body).
778	
779	\begin{definition}[Mayer-Vietoris LES on a 2-affine cover of a curve, iter-030]
780	  \label{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_HModule_prime_sequence_curve}
781	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.AffineCoverMVSquare.HModule'_sequence_curve}
782	  \uses{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_HModule_prime_sequence, def:Scheme_toModuleKSheaf}
783	  Let $k$ be a field, $C : \mathrm{Over}\,(\Spec\,(\CommRingCat.\mathrm{of}\,k))$ (a scheme over $k$), $S : C.\mathrm{left}.\AffineCoverMVSquare$, and $n_0, n_1 : \mathbb N$ with $n_0 + 1 = n_1$. The 5-term Mayer-Vietoris LES sequence on $S$ for the structure sheaf $\toModuleKSheaf\,C$ valued in $\AddCommGrpCat$ is
784	  \[
785	    S.\HModulePrimeSeqCurve\,k\,n_0\,n_1\,h
786	    \;:=\;
787	    S.\HModulePrimeSeq\,k\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)\,n_0\,n_1\,h.
788	  \]
789	\end{definition}
790	
791	\begin{theorem}[Mayer-Vietoris LES exactness on a 2-affine cover of a curve, iter-030]
792	  \label{thm:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_HModule_prime_sequence_curve_exact}
793	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.AffineCoverMVSquare.HModule'_sequence_curve_exact}
794	  \uses{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_HModule_prime_sequence_curve, thm:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_HModule_prime_sequence_exact}
795	  In the setting of Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_HModule_prime_sequence_curve}, the sequence $S.\HModulePrimeSeqCurve\,k\,n_0\,n_1\,h$ is exact.
796	\end{theorem}
797	
798	\begin{proof}
799	  By Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_HModule_prime_sequence_exact} applied to the sheaf $\toModuleKSheaf\,C$.
800	\end{proof}
801	
802	\subsection{Use in Serre finiteness}
803	
804	The iter-029 lemmas materialise Step 1 (the abstract LES) and Step 2 (the corner-identification simp lemmas) of the iter-028 Serre-finiteness sketch (Section~\ref{sec:scheme_affineCoverMVSquare}); iter-030 (this iteration) materialises Step 2.5 (the toModuleKSheaf specialisation, a routine binding so downstream code paths can reference the LES on the structure sheaf of a curve directly). The remaining work — Step 3 (the cover-totality identification on cohomology, $\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,\top \cong_{\Module k} \HModule\,k\,F\,n$, plausibly single-iteration), Step 4 (affine vanishing $H^{>0}(\Spec A, \mathcal F) = 0$, possibly multi-iteration depending on Mathlib state), and Step 5 (finiteness of each $H^0$ piece, hence of $H^1(C, \mathcal O_C)$) — is iter-031+.
